text:
Twelfth Avenue, east side, south from West 49th to 48th Street's, showing the old and the new frontage after the widening of this Avenue. A swath of land was sliced off of this side to provide for this marginal improvement. Close observation will show several structures remaining.

September 26, 1928
May 21, 1936

P. L. Sperr

(1) North (Hudson) River, showing construction work in progress on pier 88, off Twelfth Ave., at the foot of West 48th Street. The vantage point is West 46th Street, viewed in a northerly direction. July 23, 1932.

P. L. Sperr.

(2) The same, showing the new steel skeleton. In the left background appears the N.J. shore and skyline. March 20, 1935.

P. L. Sperr.
